Vice President Kamala Harris met with a group of women entrepreneurs in Ghana to discuss women's economic empowerment. She emphasized the importance of women's participation in economic, political, and social life, and announced the establishment of the Women in the Digital Economy Fund, a $60 million global fund aimed at addressing access, affordability, digital literacy, and gender inequality. The Bill and Melinda Gates Foundation is partnering with the US administration and investing an additional $40 million to support these goals. In total, over $1 billion is being dedicated to advancing women's economic participation across the African continent. Harris also announced the creation of the Ambassador's Advisory Council for Women Entrepreneurs, which will support and uplift women entrepreneurs in Ghana.